Fig. 4
 shows the oxidation of TMB in presence of H2O2 catalyzed by β-CD/N@GQDs where the absorbance intensity at 652 nm is well observed and the color of TMB is changed from colorless to blue color. After addition of DA as reducing agent, the blue color of oxTMB gradually decreased (Scheme 1). With the increase of DA concentration, the absorption intensity was decreased gradually in the range of 0.12–7.5 µM (Fig. 5
). The linear regression equation between the absorbance (A) and concentration (C) is A = −0.112 + 0.657C (R2 = 0.9982), and the limit of detection (LOD) is calculated and was found to 0.04 µM (S/N = 3). Moreover, the developed method was compared with some colorimetric methods for analysis of DA, and it was found that the method exhibits low detection limit and wide linear range (Table 1
).
